cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of searching for words in large collections of digitized manuscripts, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as it aims to find specific words in documents, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are covered in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper introduces an end-to-end trainable model based on deep neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
